The Mysteries of UdoIpho.

718
01:07:48,836 --> 01:07:51,605
-And Â£800, I believe, for her next.
-The ItaIian.

719
01:07:51,605 --> 01:07:53,745
Above Â£1 ,000?

720
01:07:56,344 --> 01:07:59,757
The times, the times.

721
01:08:13,595 --> 01:08:16,298
You live so quietly.

722
01:08:16,298 --> 01:08:20,837
And yet your novels are filled
with romance, danger, terror.

723
01:08:23,004 --> 01:08:24,949
Everything my life is not.

724
01:08:27,309 --> 01:08:28,480
Apparently.

725
01:08:29,277 --> 01:08:31,222
Ofwhat do you wish to write?

726
01:08:33,882 --> 01:08:35,326
Of the heart.

727
01:08:36,485 --> 01:08:38,157
Do you know it?

728
01:08:39,321 --> 01:08:40,800
Not all of it.

729
01:08:41,957 --> 01:08:43,731
In time, you will.

730
01:08:44,626 --> 01:08:49,040
But even ifthat fails,
that's what the imagination is for.

731
01:08:53,235 --> 01:08:56,545
Your imagination has brought you independence.

732
01:08:58,373 --> 01:09:02,252
At a cost to myself and to my husband.

733
01:09:03,678 --> 01:09:04,918
Poor William.

734
01:09:05,914 --> 01:09:08,817
To have a wife who has a mind
is considered not quite proper.

735
01:09:08,817 --> 01:09:12,924
To have a wife with a literary reputation
nothing short of scandalous.

736
01:09:18,326 --> 01:09:20,362
But it must be possible?

737
01:09:21,396 --> 01:09:24,103
-To live as both wife and author?
-Oh.

738
01:09:25,100 --> 01:09:26,340
I think so.

739
01:09:28,370 --> 01:09:29,780
Though never easy.

740
01:09:50,592 --> 01:09:52,537
(SNORING)

741
01:10:08,376 --> 01:10:10,116
Could I really have this?

742
01:10:10,912 --> 01:10:12,447
What, precisely?

743
01:10:13,448 --> 01:10:14,790
(LAUGHS) You.

744
01:10:15,784 --> 01:10:17,058
Me, how?

745
01:10:18,987 --> 01:10:20,966
-This life with you.
-Yes.

746
01:10:23,158 --> 01:10:24,492
HENRY: Lefroy.

747
01:10:24,492 --> 01:10:26,828
-Hush. The judge.
-The man's like a rampant dog.

748
01:10:26,828 --> 01:10:28,307
(SIGHS)

749
01:10:30,565 --> 01:10:33,238
He will be generous. I'm sure of it.

750
01:10:34,469 --> 01:10:37,005
-You'll speak with him?
-Tomorrow, I promise.

751
01:10:37,005 --> 01:10:39,314
I really must say good night.

752
01:10:40,075 --> 01:10:42,248
-Good night.
-Good night.

753
01:10:44,613 --> 01:10:47,423
-Miss Austen?
-Yes?

754
01:10:48,016 --> 01:10:49,460
Good night.

755
01:10:55,657 --> 01:11:00,469
You know, I think my mother is right.
A husband, and the sooner, the better.

756
01:11:39,634 --> 01:11:42,410
(BELL TOLLING)

757
01:11:45,573 --> 01:11:49,851
Five girls of little fortune.

758
01:11:58,554 --> 01:12:04,766
JANE: "...sensibIy and as warmIy as a man
vioIentIy in Iove can be supposed to do.

759
01:12:06,329 --> 01:12:11,335
"Mr Wickham was the happy man towards
whom aImost every femaIe eye was turned.

760
01:12:17,340 --> 01:12:20,582
"...partiaI, prejudiced, absurd.

761
01:12:21,577 --> 01:12:24,751
"Watch for the first appearance
of PemberIey Woods.

762
01:12:27,416 --> 01:12:29,518
"The happiness which this repIy produced...

763
01:12:29,518 --> 01:12:33,295
"It wiII not do. My feeIings wiII not be repressed."

764
01:13:14,797 --> 01:13:17,573
(CLOCK CHIMING)

765
01:13:24,407 --> 01:13:27,820
-Good morning, sir.
-Good morning?

766
01:13:32,248 --> 01:13:35,422
-Has the world turned topsy?
-Sir?

767
01:13:37,186 --> 01:13:40,189
I trust the countess is enjoying her visit?

768
01:13:40,523 --> 01:13:44,994
-(STAMMERING) I gather she is, sir. I...
-Fine woman, very fine woman.

769
01:13:46,495 --> 01:13:47,701
TOM: Indeed.

770
01:13:48,130 --> 01:13:53,136
-I'd hoped to discuss a certain matter.
-Your allowance is beyond negotiation.

771
01:13:58,974 --> 01:14:04,013
Now that you have had the opportunity
to become acquainted with Miss Austen yourself,

772
01:14:04,013 --> 01:14:08,684
I am sure you will find, as I do,
that she is a remarkable young woman.

773
01:14:08,684 --> 01:14:09,992
(EXCLAIMS)

774
01:14:11,787 --> 01:14:14,490
-This is an outrage!
-Ifyou will allow me to speak, sir.

775
01:14:14,490 --> 01:14:18,294
There is no need.
This letter makes it absolutely clear.

776
01:14:18,294 --> 01:14:19,462
Letter?

777
01:14:19,462 --> 01:14:22,704
Now I know what you were at down in Hampshire.

778
01:14:23,232 --> 01:14:25,067
-It is from Steventon.
-Is it true

779
01:14:25,067 --> 01:14:27,536
that you have practiced upon me with this chit?

780
01:14:27,536 --> 01:14:29,472
I wished you to know the young lady.

781
01:14:29,472 --> 01:14:31,574
I wished to introduce her
to your affections discreetly.

782
01:14:31,574 --> 01:14:38,481
Aye! Blind me with the rich widow and then
insinuate that penniless little husband-hunter!

783
01:14:38,481 --> 01:14:42,384
-Moderation, sir, I beg you!
-That ironical little authoress.

784
01:14:42,384 --> 01:14:44,921
I wished you to know her for yourself.

785
01:14:45,521 --> 01:14:48,365
I was certain her merit would speak for her.

786
01:14:48,591 --> 01:14:52,504
-Consider, sir, my happiness is in your hands.
-Happiness?

787
01:14:55,431 --> 01:14:56,565
Damn it, nephew,

788
01:14:56,565 --> 01:15:00,503
I had rather you were a whore-mongering
blackguard with a chance of reform

789
01:15:00,503 --> 01:15:04,280
than a love-sick whelp sunk in a bad marriage.

790
01:15:20,055 --> 01:15:22,899
My uncle has refused to give his consent.

791
01:15:24,059 --> 01:15:27,233
-The letter has done its work.
-Who sent it?

792
01:15:30,299 --> 01:15:31,800
Lady Gresham?

793
01:15:33,435 --> 01:15:34,811
Or her nephew.

794
01:15:43,479 --> 01:15:47,650
They think that they can do what they like
with us, but I will not accept this.

795
01:15:47,650 --> 01:15:49,459
We have no choice.

796
01:15:50,554 --> 01:15:52,124
Of course we do.

797
01:15:55,926 --> 01:15:57,063
I...

798
01:16:04,167 --> 01:16:07,409
I depend entirely upon...

799
01:16:13,577 --> 01:16:15,613
Upon your uncle.

800
01:16:16,446 --> 01:16:17,822
Mmm.

801
01:16:19,583 --> 01:16:21,426
And I depend on you.

802
01:16:28,024 --> 01:16:29,935
So what will you do?

803
01:16:32,963 --> 01:16:34,442
What I must.

804
01:16:35,332 --> 01:16:39,869
I have a duty to my family, Jane.
I must think of them as well as...

805
01:16:39,869 --> 01:16:40,972
Tom...

806
01:16:44,841 --> 01:16:47,878
Is that... Is that all you have to say to me?

807
01:17:04,561 --> 01:17:06,233
Goodbye, Mr Lefroy.

808
01:18:01,251 --> 01:18:05,221
The sentence ofthis court is that you be taken
to the place whence you came

809
01:18:05,221 --> 01:18:08,634
and thence to a place of execution,

810
01:18:09,125 --> 01:18:13,903
and that you be there hanged by the neck
until you are dead.

811
01:18:14,864 --> 01:18:17,640
May the Lord have mercy on your soul.

812
01:18:26,976 --> 01:18:28,216
Next.

813
01:18:40,924 --> 01:18:43,666
He has behaved so ill to you, Jane.

814
01:18:49,165 --> 01:18:52,271
Perhaps soon we can return home to Steventon.

815
01:18:54,571 --> 01:18:56,641
Is there any news of Robert?

816
01:19:03,346 --> 01:19:05,715
He has arrived in San Domingo at last.

817
01:19:05,715 --> 01:19:06,886
Good.

818
01:19:09,018 --> 01:19:10,087
Good.

819
01:19:34,978 --> 01:19:37,424
Glass ofwine with you, sir?

820
01:19:39,082 --> 01:19:40,151
Yes.

821
01:19:40,750 --> 01:19:44,060
Yes, a toast from one member
ofthe profession to another.

822
01:20:59,663 --> 01:21:03,133
I'm sorry to have been so disobliging in the past.

823
01:21:09,006 --> 01:21:10,507
Mr Wisley?

824
01:21:16,247 --> 01:21:19,853
So, the infamous Mrs Radcliffe.

825
01:21:20,351 --> 01:21:23,161
Was she really as gothic as her novels?

826
01:21:26,090 --> 01:21:28,392
Not in externals,

827
01:21:28,392 --> 01:21:31,428
but her inner landscape is quite picturesque,
I suspect.

828
01:21:31,428 --> 01:21:32,998
True of us all.

829
01:22:32,056 --> 01:22:34,627
(WHISPERING) There's a message
for Reverend Austen.

830
01:22:39,063 --> 01:22:42,738
-(WHISPERING) Message for Reverend Austen.
-Thank you.

831
01:23:08,425 --> 01:23:09,767
ELIZA: Uncle?

832
01:23:26,110 --> 01:23:27,520
What is it?

833
01:23:32,983 --> 01:23:35,963
(SOBBING)

834
01:24:03,181 --> 01:24:05,820
(GASPING)

835
01:24:28,773 --> 01:24:32,448
It seemed he died very soon
after landing in San Domingo.

836
01:24:32,744 --> 01:24:35,019
My God, he was hardly there.

837
01:24:35,947 --> 01:24:37,892
What was the disease?

838
01:24:39,184 --> 01:24:42,961
Yellow fever. Lord Craven, he wrote.

839
01:24:43,388 --> 01:24:46,758
He said that if he had known
he was engaged to be married,

840
01:24:46,758 --> 01:24:49,067
he would never have taken him.

841
01:24:56,134 --> 01:24:58,910
Jane, there's something else.

842
01:25:00,638 --> 01:25:02,981
Mr Lefroy, Tom.

843
01:25:05,110 --> 01:25:06,213
What?

844
01:25:06,978 --> 01:25:09,981
I would keep this from you if I could.

845
01:25:10,148 --> 01:25:13,128
He's here visiting Mrs Lefroy and I...

846
01:25:13,251 --> 01:25:14,923
He is engaged.

847
01:25:25,430 --> 01:25:26,636
So soon?

848
01:26:00,265 --> 01:26:01,505
A letter?

849
01:26:03,835 --> 01:26:05,006
No.

850
01:26:05,570 --> 01:26:08,175
It's something I began in London.

851
01:26:12,577 --> 01:26:15,614
It is the tale of a young woman.

852
01:26:16,314 --> 01:26:17,986
Two young women.

853
01:26:20,318 --> 01:26:22,354
Better than their circumstances.

854
01:26:22,787 --> 01:26:24,355
So many are.

855
01:26:24,355 --> 01:26:27,335
And two young gentlemen who receive

856
01:26:27,826 --> 01:26:31,136
much better than their deserts
as so very many do.

857
01:26:33,264 --> 01:26:34,504
Mmm.

858
01:26:38,870 --> 01:26:40,679
How does the story begin?

859
01:26:41,272 --> 01:26:42,841
-Badly.
-And then?

860
01:26:42,841 --> 01:26:44,513
It gets worse.

861
01:26:46,277 --> 01:26:48,188
With, I hope, some humour.

862
01:26:54,052 --> 01:26:55,690
How does it end?

863
01:27:01,726 --> 01:27:04,229
They both make triumphant, happy endings.

864
01:27:06,497 --> 01:27:08,169
Brilliant marriages?

865
01:27:09,300 --> 01:27:11,643
Incandescent marriages

866
01:27:13,238 --> 01:27:14,978
to very rich men.

867
01:27:27,986 --> 01:27:31,490
You asked me a question.

868
01:27:32,490 --> 01:27:37,166
I am ready to give you an answer.
But there is one matter to be settled.

869
01:27:40,899 --> 01:27:43,174
I cannot make you out, Mr Wisley.

870
01:27:45,203 --> 01:27:46,910
At times, you are

871
01:27:47,873 --> 01:27:51,076
the most gentlemanlike man I know
and yet you would...

872
01:27:51,076 --> 01:27:53,852
"Yet". What a sad word.

873
01:27:54,914 --> 01:27:59,760
And yet, you write yourself
most tellingly to great effect.

874
01:28:01,220 --> 01:28:04,623
-I'm speaking, of course, ofyour letter.
-What letter?

875
01:28:04,623 --> 01:28:07,899
Was your aunt the correspondent on your behalf?

876
01:28:09,929 --> 01:28:11,408
What matter?

877
01:28:12,398 --> 01:28:14,934
One way or another,
passion makes fools of us all.

878
01:28:14,934 --> 01:28:17,436
I hope, in time,
passion may regain your better opinion.

879
01:28:17,436 --> 01:28:19,415
The emotion is absurd.

880
01:28:20,372 --> 01:28:23,309
When you consider
the sex to whom it is often directed,

881
01:28:23,309 --> 01:28:25,721
indistinguishable from folly.

882
01:28:27,713 --> 01:28:31,820
I thank you for the honour ofyour proposal.
I accept. Good day.

883
01:28:58,844 --> 01:29:00,414
George, George.

884
01:29:01,080 --> 01:29:04,683
Mr Wisley is... He's an honourable man.

885
01:29:04,683 --> 01:29:06,856
You'll always have a place with me.

886
01:29:07,353 --> 01:29:08,661
(GRUNTS)

887
01:29:12,491 --> 01:29:13,867
Miss Austen.

888
01:29:16,128 --> 01:29:17,663
Mr Lefroy.

889
01:29:26,672 --> 01:29:27,843
Sir.

890
01:29:32,144 --> 01:29:35,614
I believe I must congratulate you, Mr Lefroy.

891
01:29:37,316 --> 01:29:41,320
And you've come to visit an old friend
at such a time. How considerate.

892
01:29:47,826 --> 01:29:51,063
I have come

893
01:29:51,063 --> 01:29:54,009
to offer an explanation, belatedly,

894
01:29:55,134 --> 01:29:59,171
for my conduct. I cannot think how to describe it.

895
01:29:59,171 --> 01:30:01,742
Tell me about your lady, Mr Lefroy.

896
01:30:03,042 --> 01:30:05,112
From where does she come?

897
01:30:07,179 --> 01:30:09,352
She's from County Wexford.

898
01:30:09,715 --> 01:30:12,718
Your own country. Excellent.

899
01:30:15,120 --> 01:30:20,569
What was it that won her?
Your manner, smiles and pleasing address?

900
01:30:26,465 --> 01:30:29,445
No, no, not at all.

901
01:30:29,601 --> 01:30:36,241
No, had I really experienced that emotion,
I should, at present, detest the very sight of him.

902
01:30:36,241 --> 01:30:38,210
And you are mistaken.

903
01:30:38,210 --> 01:30:42,781
I'm even impartial towards
the gloriously endowed Miss Wexford...

904
01:30:42,781 --> 01:30:44,453
I cannot do this.

905
01:30:54,426 --> 01:30:56,633
And so you would marry Wisley?

906
01:31:02,134 --> 01:31:03,908
(WHISPERS) Please?

907
01:31:07,072 --> 01:31:11,176
If there is a shred of truth
or justice inside ofyou,

908
01:31:11,176 --> 01:31:13,479
-you cannot marry him.
-Oh no, Mr Lefroy.

909
01:31:13,479 --> 01:31:16,515
Justice, by your own admission,
you know little of, truth even less.

910
01:31:16,515 --> 01:31:21,122
Jane, I have tried.
I have tried and I cannot live this lie.

911
01:31:22,121 --> 01:31:23,429
Can you?

912
01:31:24,523 --> 01:31:26,935
Jane, can you?

913
01:31:30,996 --> 01:31:34,636
What value will there be in life
ifwe are not together?

914
01:31:42,107 --> 01:31:43,984
Run away with me.

915
01:31:46,513 --> 01:31:48,219
An elopement?

916
01:31:49,182 --> 01:31:51,525
That is exactly what I propose.

917
01:31:52,619 --> 01:31:57,226
We'll post to London,
by Friday be in Scotland, and man and wife.

918
01:31:59,726 --> 01:32:02,206
-Leave everything?
-Everything.

919
01:32:03,062 --> 01:32:05,565
It is the only way we can be together.

920
01:32:25,585 --> 01:32:27,655
You'll lose everything.

921
01:32:28,321 --> 01:32:32,769
Family, place. Forwhat?

922
01:32:33,193 --> 01:32:35,935
A lifetime of drudgery on a pittance?

923
01:32:36,663 --> 01:32:40,042
A child every year
and no means to lighten the load?

924
01:32:40,333 --> 01:32:43,370
-How will you write, Jane?
-I do not know.

925
01:32:43,770 --> 01:32:46,773
But happiness is within my grasp
and I cannot help myself.

926
01:32:46,773 --> 01:32:48,912
There is no sense in this.

927
01:32:53,246 --> 01:32:57,751
Ifyou could have your Robert back, even like this,

928
01:32:58,851 --> 01:33:00,523
would you do it?

929
01:33:05,225 --> 01:33:06,760
(EXCLAIMS)

930
01:33:07,594 --> 01:33:11,598
-Please conceal my departure as long as possible.
-Wait.

931
01:33:14,300 --> 01:33:15,540
Here.

932
01:33:17,570 --> 01:33:19,879
Take these. Now go, quickly.

933
01:33:55,742 --> 01:33:59,519
Come. Ifwe hurry,
we can still make the morning coach.

934
01:33:59,846 --> 01:34:01,188
You are sure?

935
01:34:07,920 --> 01:34:09,262
Be careful.

936
01:34:11,424 --> 01:34:14,166
-Is it coming?
-Not yet.

937
01:34:16,863 --> 01:34:20,139
Take my hand. All right?

938
01:34:20,533 --> 01:34:23,013
Hurry. I can hear it approaching.

939
01:34:28,207 --> 01:34:29,549
Here it is.

940
01:34:36,883 --> 01:34:38,327
Whoa.

941
01:34:39,385 --> 01:34:41,654
Two to London. We'll settle the first rest.

942
01:34:41,654 --> 01:34:43,497
-Yes?
-Right you are, sir.

943
01:35:15,221 --> 01:35:17,496
Hampshire, your home county.

944
01:35:19,092 --> 01:35:20,434
It was.

945
01:35:24,230 --> 01:35:25,709
(LAUGHING)

946
01:35:26,599 --> 01:35:28,043
(RUMBLING)

947
01:35:30,002 --> 01:35:33,847
Stuck. Everybody out,
ladies and gentlemen, please.

948
01:35:35,608 --> 01:35:38,211
-We need to lighten the load.
-No, let me, let me.

949
01:35:38,211 --> 01:35:43,217
COACHMAN: I shall require you gentlemen
to give me a hand, put your shoulders into it.

950
01:35:45,586 --> 01:35:50,865
Now, sir, ifyou can push on the coach itself.
Excuse me, sir. Young gentleman?

951
01:35:51,024 --> 01:35:53,902
-Yes, yes.
-You on the other side, sir, thank you.

952
01:35:54,395 --> 01:35:56,864
-Young gentleman, please come along.
-All right.

953
01:35:56,864 --> 01:35:59,276
COACHMAN: Mind helping us? Thank you.

954
01:35:59,700 --> 01:36:02,373
Right, all together now then, sirs, please?

955
01:36:03,737 --> 01:36:06,308
(MEN GRUNTING)

956
01:36:07,541 --> 01:36:09,111
One, two,

957
01:36:09,877 --> 01:36:11,617
and a three and push!

958
01:36:12,746 --> 01:36:14,054
Come on.

959
01:36:15,416 --> 01:36:17,054
MRS LEFROY: "Dear Tom.

960
01:36:17,451 --> 01:36:20,431
"How timeIy was the arrivaI
of the money you sent."

961
01:36:22,256 --> 01:36:24,895
COACHMAN: One, two and three!

962
01:36:29,997 --> 01:36:33,444
"It was so very much appreciated
by your father and I.

963
01:36:34,067 --> 01:36:37,404
"You're so kind to share your uncIe's aIIowance.

964
01:36:37,404 --> 01:36:40,007
"Indeed, I do not dare think
how we wouId survive without it."

965
01:36:40,007 --> 01:36:41,247
(GRUNTS)

966
01:36:46,980 --> 01:36:49,084
Well done. Thank you, sirs.

967
01:36:49,616 --> 01:36:54,064
All right, ladies and gentlemen, back on
the coach as soon as you can, thank you.

968
01:37:03,864 --> 01:37:05,399
We are ready.

969
01:37:11,805 --> 01:37:14,046
-Worried?
-No.

970
01:37:15,576 --> 01:37:19,546
-Is it the loss ofyour reputation?
-No.

971
01:37:21,648 --> 01:37:23,183
The loss ofyours.

972
01:37:23,183 --> 01:37:27,187
-I do not...
-Please, sir, come along, the coach is departing.

973
01:37:27,187 --> 01:37:28,393
Come.

974
01:38:04,591 --> 01:38:07,261
COACHMAN: Changing horses.
Twenty minutes only.

975
01:38:07,261 --> 01:38:11,607
House of office at the back of the inn.
All down, quick as you like.

976
01:38:34,054 --> 01:38:37,791
How many brothers and sisters
do you have in Limerick, Tom?

977
01:38:37,791 --> 01:38:40,168
Enough. Why?

978
01:38:43,564 --> 01:38:46,400
What are the names ofyour brothers and sisters?

979
01:38:46,400 --> 01:38:47,810
They...

980
01:38:51,405 --> 01:38:53,578
On whom do they depend?

981
01:38:57,644 --> 01:38:58,912
(SIGHS)

982
01:38:58,912 --> 01:39:00,948
Your reputation is destroyed.

983
01:39:03,650 --> 01:39:07,120
Your profligacy is a beautiful sham.

984
01:39:18,932 --> 01:39:22,311
-I can earn money.
-It will not be enough.

985
01:39:24,338 --> 01:39:25,873
I will rise.

986
01:39:26,707 --> 01:39:30,484
With a High Court Judge as your enemy?
And a penniless wife?

987
01:39:31,678 --> 01:39:34,681
God knows how many mouths depending on you?

988
01:39:36,049 --> 01:39:40,725
My sweet, sweet friend,
